<paragraph id="626EE6082500FFBF76A3FCC6FB8E7D47" blockId="3.[178,1086,1414,1582]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060">
This species has been treated for a long period as junior subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="A5D19D8B2500FFBF75F1FCC7FE077ED0" authority="(SCHAUM 1857)" baseAuthorityName="SCHAUM" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lernaeus">
<emphasis id="50A53A1A2500FFBF75F1FCC7FEBA7ED0" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060">Hygrotus lernaeus</emphasis>
(SCHAUM 1857)
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92500FFBF77E0FCE3FD7E7ED0" author="GUIGNOT F" box="[497,717,1443,1465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" pagination="323 - 648" refId="ref4814" refString="GUIGNOT F. (1959 a): Revision des hydrocanthares d'Afrique (Coleoptera Dytiscoidea). 2. - Annales du Musee Royal du Congo Belge Tervuren (Belgique), Serie 8 vo, Sciences Zoologiques 78: 323 - 648." type="journal article" year="1959">GUIGNOT 1959a: 332</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92500FFBF74C8FCE4FC6A7ED0" author="FRANCISCOLO M" box="[729,985,1443,1465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" pagination="1 - 804" refId="ref4745" refString="FRANCISCOLO M. E. (1979): Coleoptera, Haliplidae, Hygrobiidae, Gyrinidae, Dytiscidae. - Fauna d'Italia 14: 1 - 804." type="journal article" year="1979">FRANCISCOLO 1979: 310</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92500FFBF75F4FCE4FEA97EBF" author="NILSSON A" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" refId="ref5165" refString="NILSSON A. N. (2001): World catalogue of insects. Vol. 3. Dytiscidae Coleoptera. - Stenstrup: Apollo Books, 395 pp." type="book" year="2001">NILSSON 2001: 207</bibRefCitation>
) or as variety of the latter (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92500FFBF7472FC81FCD07EBF" author="ZIMMERMANN A" box="[611,867,1472,1494]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" pagination="35 - 118" refId="ref5888" refString="ZIMMERMANN A. (1930): Monographie der palaarktischen Dytisciden. I. Noterinae, Laccophilinae, Hydroporinae (1. Teil). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 16: 35 - 118." type="journal article" year="1930">ZIMMERMANN 1930: 101</bibRefCitation>
) or misinterpreted as this species (HOSSEINIE 1976: 169; 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92500FFBF740BFC9EFD127E9D" author="ALI H" box="[538,673,1502,1524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" pagination="11 - 14" refId="ref4438" refString="ALI H. A. (1978): A list of some aquatic beetles of Iraq (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). - Bulletin of the Natural History Research Centre 7 (2): 11 - 14." type="journal article" year="1978">ALI 1978: 12</bibRefCitation>
; AL- HOUTY &amp; 
<collectingRegion id="A01528EA2500FFBF752CFC9EFC367E9B" box="[829,901,1502,1524]" country="United Kingdom" name="Angus" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060">ANGUS</collectingRegion>
1999: 184). 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92500FFBF7216FC9EFE9C7D78" author="FERY H &amp; SADEGHI L" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" pagination="29 - 44" refId="ref4682" refString="FERY H., SADEGHI L. &amp; S. O. HOSSEINIE (2005): Hygrotus curvilobus sp. n. and H. stefanschoedli sp. n. from Iran, and re-instatement of H. orthogrammus (SHARP, 1882) as valid species (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 29 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">FERY et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
re-instated this taxon as valid species. It is indeed externally very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A5D19D8B2500FFBF76A3FF59FE9A7D47" baseAuthorityName="SCHAUM" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[178,297,1560,1582]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lernaeus">
<emphasis id="50A53A1A2500FFBF76A3FF59FE9A7D47" box="[178,297,1560,1582]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1060">H. lernaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the other hand both are easily to separate by the shape of the prosternal
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2ACBB5832507FFB876A3F99BFC2B7A91" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" type="description">
<paragraph id="626EE6082507FFB876A3F99BFC2B7A91" blockId="4.[178,1085,219,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">
process which is almost flat in 
<taxonomicName id="A5D19D8B2507FFB877E9F99BFD1F7B98" baseAuthorityName="SHARP" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[504,684,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orthogrammus">
<emphasis id="50A53A1A2507FFB877E9F99BFD1F7B98" box="[504,684,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">H. orthogrammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinctly carinate in 
<taxonomicName id="A5D19D8B2507FFB875D1F99BFB857B98" baseAuthorityName="SCHAUM" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[960,1078,219,241]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lernaeus">
<emphasis id="50A53A1A2507FFB875D1F99BFB857B98" box="[960,1078,219,241]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">H. lernaeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the shape of the female gonocoxae is also specifically different (
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92507FFB8754AF9B8FB8A7A67" author="FERY H &amp; SADEGHI L" box="[859,1081,248,270]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" pagination="29 - 44" refId="ref4682" refString="FERY H., SADEGHI L. &amp; S. O. HOSSEINIE (2005): Hygrotus curvilobus sp. n. and H. stefanschoedli sp. n. from Iran, and re-instatement of H. orthogrammus (SHARP, 1882) as valid species (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 29 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">FERY et al. 2005: 40</bibRefCitation>
, figs 12 and 13). The species is well-known from 
<collectingCountry id="1AC6A6982507FFB874D1F856FD587A42" box="[704,747,278,299]" name="Iraq" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iraq</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1AC6A6982507FFB874E8F855FCF57A42" box="[761,838,277,299]" name="Kuwait" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="1AC6A6982507FFB87545F855FC6F7A42" box="[852,988,277,299]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
and also from the 
<collectingRegion id="A01528EA2507FFB87706F872FE557A21" box="[279,486,306,328]" country="Iran" name="Khuzestan" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Khuzestan province</collectingRegion>
(among others) in 
<collectingCountry id="1AC6A6982507FFB874A9F873FD527A21" box="[696,737,307,328]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92507FFB874E3F872FC667A21" author="FERY H &amp; SADEGHI L" box="[754,981,306,328]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" pagination="29 - 44" refId="ref4682" refString="FERY H., SADEGHI L. &amp; S. O. HOSSEINIE (2005): Hygrotus curvilobus sp. n. and H. stefanschoedli sp. n. from Iran, and re-instatement of H. orthogrammus (SHARP, 1882) as valid species (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). - Koleopterologische Rundschau 75: 29 - 44." type="journal article" year="2005">FERY et al. 2005: 37</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92507FFB875F4F873FEA37A0F" author="NILSSON A" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" refId="ref5260" refString="NILSSON A. N. (2012): Catalogue of Palearctic Dytiscidae (Coleoptera). Internet version 2012 - 01 - 01. - Available from http: // www 2. emg. umu. se / projects / biginst / andersn / Cat main. htm (accessed in August 2012)." type="url" year="2012">NILSSON 2012: 43</bibRefCitation>
). Although the following record is not the first one for 
<collectingCountry id="1AC6A6982507FFB8755CF810FCCB7A0C" box="[845,888,336,357]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iran</collectingCountry>
, it is included here because it completes well the older records of this little known species: 1, 1, &quot; 
<date id="166FC0C82507FFB876ABF8CAFE927AC9" box="[186,289,394,416]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" value="2010-06-12">6.12.2010</date>
<collectingCountry id="1AC6A6982507FFB87738F8CBFEE77AC9" box="[297,340,395,416]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Iran</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion id="A01528EA2507FFB8774EF8CAFE7F7AC9" box="[351,460,394,416]" country="Iran" name="Khuzestan" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Khuzestan</collectingRegion>
, 
<quantity id="A5294BED2507FFB877C6F8CAFDAB7AC9" box="[471,536,394,416]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" unit="km" value="10.0">10 km</quantity>
N Bandare Emam, ca. 
<geoCoordinate id="07E580CF2507FFB87516F8CAFCE17AC9" box="[775,850,394,416]" degrees="30.58" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" precision="555" value="30.58">30.58N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="07E580CF2507FFB87548F8CAFC177AC9" box="[857,932,394,416]" degrees="49.05" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" precision="555" value="49.05">49.05E</geoCoordinate>
, altitude 
<quantity id="A5294BED2507FFB87212F8CAFB8A7AC9" box="[1027,1081,394,416]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" unit="m" value="21.0">21 m</quantity>
, basin, Darvishzadeh leg.&quot; (CHF) (
<figureCitation id="FAEAFA8D2507FFB87403F8E7FDEC7AD4" box="[530,607,423,445]" captionStart="Fig 23" captionStartId="2.[178,212,219,241]" captionText="Fig 23). The label data are: &quot;21.7.2011 Iran, Hormozgan prov., NE Bandar Abbas, ca. 5 km ENE Rudan (Roodān), Rudan stream, 27.4771N 57.2578E, alt. 210 m, pump in gravels, Pešić leg. (IR22)&quot;, &quot;Glareadessus franzi Wewalka &amp; Biström, Fery det. 2011&quot; (CHF). This collecting site is illustrated in Fig. 21; it is situated only about 25 km west of the type locality. A comparison with a photo of the locus typicus in WEWALKA &amp; BISTRÖM (1998: 63; fig. 12) shows that both localities appear rather similar. Another female has been found (also by means of a pump) ca. 60 km WNW of Rudan (triangle (1) in Fig. 23; the collecting site is illustrated in Figs 19 and 20); the label data are: &quot;18.7.2011 Iran, Hormozgan prov., N Bandar Abass, Banglayan village, stream, 27.7616N 56.5400E, alt. 577 m, pump in gravels, Pešić leg. (IR19)&quot;, the DNA extraction voucher number &quot;IBE-RA 640&quot; and &quot;parts of abdomen lost due to sequencing&quot; and the same determination label as above (CHF)." pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
; square 2). A photo of the habitus of this species is provided here for the first time (
<figureCitation id="FAEAFA8D2507FFB8742EF885FD387AB2" box="[575,651,453,475]" captionStart="Figs 13-15" captionStartId="11.[178,218,716,736]" captionTargetBox="[190,1074,237,674]" captionTargetId="figure-79@11.[178,1084,219,696]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 13-15: Habitus of (13) Hyphoporus solieri, (14) Hygrotus orthogrammus, (15) Canthydrus laetabilis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5367840" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5367840/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). The specimens were found together with 
<taxonomicName id="A5D19D8B2507FFB876A3F8A2FDA97A91" authority="(KLUG 1834)" baseAuthorityName="KLUG" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[178,538,482,504]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="musicus">
<emphasis id="50A53A1A2507FFB876A3F8A2FE3C7A91" box="[178,399,482,504]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Herophydrus musicus</emphasis>
(KLUG 1834)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A5D19D8B2507FFB8745DF8A2FC277A91" authority="SHARP 1882" authorityName="SHARP" authorityYear="1882" box="[588,916,482,504]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hydaticus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ponticus">
<emphasis id="50A53A1A2507FFB8745DF8A2FCBC7A91" box="[588,783,482,504]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061">Hydaticus ponticus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="06409BF92507FFB87505F8A2FC277A91" author="SHARP D" box="[788,916,482,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1061" pagination="179 - 1003" refId="ref5543" refString="SHARP D. (1882) On aquatic carnivorous Coleoptera or Dytiscidae. - Scientific Transactions of the Royal Dublin Society (2) 2: 179 - 1003 + pls. 7 - 18." type="journal article" year="1882">SHARP 1882</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
